Reasoning: The paper discusses language acquisition and learning from positive evidence, which are topics commonly studied in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of a Simplicity Principle also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also presents a framework for reconsidering the learnability of natural language, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and systems and control (cs.SD).
